HEADWORD: Wannish
<hw>Wan"nish</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Somewhat wan; of a pale
hue.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>No sun, but a <qex>wannish</qex> glare,⟦br⟧
In fold upon fold of hueless cloud.</q>
<rj><qau>Tennyson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Want</ent>⟦br⟧
